						               													<description>Dice rolling game for the very young, promoting the Austrian stationery manufacturer Brevillier-Urban. The players are pencils in a snowball fight against the evil eraser pirates who are hiding in their snow fort. &amp;#10;Each player gets the same number of snow ball tokens. Then they take turns rolling a die. On a roll of 1-5, they either place a snow ball in the catapult (depicted on the game board) with the corresponding number (depicted on the game board), or, if the catapult is already occupied, they take the snowball from that catapult. On a roll of six, they land a hit and place a snow ball in the snow fort. The first player to run out of snow balls is the winner. There is no decision making what so ever; just roll the die and see what happens.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(User summary by HilkMAN)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
